&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TRUST GRADE SENIOR HOUSE OFFICER IN ANAESTHESIA (CT2 OR ABOVE)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Trust Grade Senior House Officer in Anaesthesia (CT2 or above), which will be available to start from Feb 2021 or August 2021. This post is appropriate for anyone who has completed 12 months of Anaesthesia. Initially, the successful candidate will be part of the CT1/2 rota, which is currently 1:8. Whilst the post is advertised for a CT2, any grade of anaesthetist up to ST7 can be incorporated owing to the flexible nature of the work and the rotas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whilst in post we can aid the post holder in obtaining the Primary FRCA if needed and any outstanding units of training in order to complete core training. Previous candidates have successfully gone on to training rotations at ST3.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are required to have full GMC registration/license and inclusion on the Specialist Register of the General Medical Council at the time of interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Dr Ben Graham – Site Lead for St Mary&#39;s, or Dr Emma James – Site Lead for Clinical Fellows, at emma.james15@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
